content.description: Slightly overhung jug haul.  When I first came to Maple, I expected all the easy routes to be like this.  Most of the beginner climbs turned out to be surprisingly thin and crimpy (I'm looking at you, Orangutan Wall).  This is the antidote to that: big moves and large holds.
content.protection: six bolts plus two thick hangers to rap off of
content.location: in the middle of the rightmost wall of the cove.

content.description: Slightly overhung with giant cobbles to pull on.  One of the juggiest 5.9's in maple.
content.location: Second route on the leftmost wall as you enter Lou's Tavern.

content.description:
Full-on adventure climbing for the area.  heh heh

Enough sand in the first 30-40 feet for a tacky photo shoot with some ho-bag wearing nothing but butt floss all while the surf pounds (yes, pounds) her deeper into the grit.

Expect huge holds for 8-9ish climbing up to the bulge. Then find the more forgiving angle and larger holds just left of the bolt line up top.
content.location: Right most.  Look for palm trees, sunsets, and hammocks.

content.description: Easy moves down low, then either do a few big moves on big holds, or harder moves on smaller holds to get through the crux section at the last bolt.
content.location: First route you pass as you walk into the alcove.  On your left.

content.description: Big holds up to a bulge where you have to get a little creative (crux). Once you are past the bulge, it's smooth sailing to the anchors.
content.location: Just left of Warm and Soapy, in the corner.

content.description: The harder of the pair of tits.  This one goes straight up the line.  Watch out for the tree at your back if you fall.
content.location: On to topmost wall of the alcove, just left of a big black streak.  If there's a small tree at your back, you're on the right route.

content.description: A seemingly featureless face relinquishes just enough holds to make this the easier route.  Halfway up, the tits squeeze together as you move over a guano-covered weakness to the finish.
content.protection: 2 bolts, then three more shared bolts, and two for the anchor
content.location: At the highest part of the alcove floor, just to the right of the boxy chimney.
